cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.MM 

The paper deals with supervised learning using nonnegative matrix factorization with group sparsity constraints. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and specifically involves computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) applications such as face recognition and facial expression recognition. The use of variational Bayesian algorithms also suggests a possible fit with information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
